  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2012-07-19",
    "date": "2012-09-14T21:31:09Z",
    "text": "Fostering Innovation Act - Directs the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) to redefine \"accelerated filer\" with respect to issuers of securities required to meet accelerated deadlines for filing their Form 10-Q quarterly reports.\n\nRequires the SEC to include among accelerated filers any issuers of securities that have: (1) annual revenues in excess of $100 million, and (2) an aggregated worldwide market value of the voting and non-voting common equity held by non-affiliates of between $250 million and $700 million."
  },
